io.swagger.transform.migrate

Interface SwaggerMigrator

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    ApiArrayMigrator, ApiObjectMigrator, ApiOperationMigrator, OperationParametersMigrator, PathAppenderMigrator, SwaggerMigrators.MembersToString, V11AllowableValuesMigrator, V11ApiDeclarationMigrator, V11ResourceListingMigrator, V11TypeMigrator

    public interface SwaggerMigrator
    Core interface for JSON migration

    This takes a JsonNode as an input and outputs the transformed JsonNode.

    Note that this interface makes no guarantee as to whether a new JsonNode is returned, or the input argument is returned (altered or not). If this distinction is important, please document it in your implementation(s).

    You can either implement this interface directly or use one of the predefined migrators in SwaggerMigrators.

    See Also:
    SwaggerMigrators, MutableJsonTree.applyMigrator(SwaggerMigrator), MutableJsonTree.applyMigratorToElements(SwaggerMigrator)
